# Figma → Kalfa.me implementation rules

Stack reference: Laravel 12+, PHP 8.4, Livewire 4, Flux UI (`<flux:*>`), TallStackUI (`<x-*>` where already used), Alpine.js, Tailwind CSS v4 (Vite + `@tailwindcss/vite`), Blade.

## 1. Design tokens

- **Source of truth:** `resources/css/app.css` inside the `@theme { ... }` block.
- **Brand & semantic colors** are exposed as CSS variables (e.g. `--color-brand`, `--color-surface`, `--color-card`, `--color-stroke`, `--color-content`, `--color-content-muted`, `--color-success`, `--color-warning`, `--color-danger`) and map to Tailwind utilities such as `bg-brand`, `text-content`, `border-stroke`.
- **IMPORTANT:** Do not introduce arbitrary hex colors for UI that should match the product. Prefer existing theme utilities; extend `@theme` only when adding a deliberate new token.
- **Dark mode:** `.dark` overrides in `app.css` update the same variables. Use `dark:` variants and test both themes.
- **Component-layer primitives** live in `@layer components` in the same file (`.btn-primary`, `.card`, `.input-base`, `.nav-link`, auth shells, etc.). Prefer these classes when they match the design before inventing new one-off utilities.

## 2. Component library & file placement

- **Flux UI:** Use `<flux:...>` for forms, modals, tables, fields, and other interactive Livewire UI per existing pages. Follow `fluxui-development` / project conventions.
- **Blade components:** Shared non-Flux pieces go in `resources/views/components/` (e.g. `x-page-header`, `x-ent-side-bar`, buttons, icons).
- **Livewire:** PHP classes in `app/Livewire/` (namespaced by area: `Dashboard/`, `Billing/`, `System/`, etc.). Views in `resources/views/livewire/` mirroring the component name/path; some v4 SFC-style components live under `resources/views/components/...` with `⚡` naming—match siblings in the same feature.
- **Layouts:** `resources/views/components/layouts/enterprise-app.blade.php` (main app), `guest.blade.php`, `app.blade.php`, `mobile-shell.blade.php`. New authenticated dashboard pages should use the same layout pattern as neighboring features (`->layout('components.layouts.enterprise-app')` or equivalent).
- **IMPORTANT:** Search for an existing Flux component or Blade partial before adding duplicate markup.

## 3. Styling approach

- **Tailwind v4** via `@import "tailwindcss"` in `resources/css/app.css`; no legacy `tailwind.config.js` theme duplication for core tokens.
- **Flux styles** are imported from `vendor/livewire/flux/dist/flux.css` in `app.css`—do not fork vendor CSS.
- **Responsive:** Mobile-first utilities; app shell uses `lg:` breakpoints for sidebar vs drawer (see `enterprise-app` layout).
- **RTL:** `dir` is set from `isRTL()` on `<html>`. Use logical properties and Tailwind `start`/`end` variants where relevant; avoid hard-coded `left`/`right` for layout that must mirror.

## 4. Frameworks & build

- **Vite** entry: `resources/css/app.css`, `resources/js/app.js` (see `vite.config.js`). After CSS/markup changes, `npm run dev` or `npm run build` as appropriate.
- **JS:** Path alias `@` → `resources/js` for any new TypeScript/JS modules.

## 5. Icons

- **IMPORTANT:** Prefer existing Blade icon components in `resources/views/components/` (`heroicon-o-*`) or Flux/Livewire patterns already used in the file.
- Do not add new icon npm packages for Figma exports if the Figma MCP provides SVG assets—use provided assets or existing Heroicons-style components.

## 6. Assets & media

- **Static build assets:** `public/` and Vite-processed files under `public/build/`.
- **User/org media:** Spatie Media Library on models—use existing collections and helpers; do not bypass established upload components without a product reason.
- **Figma MCP:** If the server returns a localhost URL for an image/SVG, use it during implementation as documented by the MCP; store durable assets under the project’s normal `public` or media flow for production.

## 7. Routing, auth, and tenancy

- Use **named routes** and `route()` in Blade/Livewire.
- Many dashboard routes use middleware such as `ensure.organization` and billing gates (`ensure.account_active`, etc.). New pages must align with the same middleware stack as similar features.
- **Strings:** User-visible copy via `__('messages.key')` / lang files in `resources/lang/` (en/he). Do not hardcode English/Hebrew in a way that breaks localization.

## 8. Figma MCP integration (required flow)

Use the **official Figma MCP** (e.g. `get_design_context`, `get_screenshot`, `get_metadata`) for Figma-driven work.

1. Run **`get_design_context`** for the exact node(s) to implement.
2. If the payload is truncated or too large, run **`get_metadata`**, then fetch only needed nodes with **`get_design_context`**.
3. Run **`get_screenshot`** for visual reference of the variant being built.
4. Only after design context + screenshot, pull assets if needed, then implement.
5. **Translate** MCP output (often React + Tailwind) into this stack: Blade + Livewire + Flux/Tailwind v4 + existing components—not copy-paste as React.
6. Validate **1:1** against the screenshot (spacing, typography, states, dark mode).

### Implementation expectations

- Treat MCP-generated code as a **design spec**, not final style or file structure.
- Map Figma colors to **`@theme`** tokens and utilities in `app.css`.
- Reuse **`.btn-*`, `.card`, `.input-base`, `.badge-*`, `.nav-link`** when they fit.
- Preserve **accessibility** (labels, focus rings, skip link patterns consistent with layouts).

## 9. Testing & quality

- **IMPORTANT:** Programmatic tests are required for behavioral changes (PHPUnit feature tests per project rules). Purely visual tweaks may still need smoke or Livewire tests if logic or routes change.
- Run **`./vendor/bin/pint --dirty`** on modified PHP before finishing.

## 10. What not to do

- Do not add standalone React/Vue components for main product UI unless the repo already does so for that feature.
- Do not hardcode theme colors outside the token system without updating `@theme`.
- Do not skip organization/billing middleware patterns when adding dashboard routes.
